          <abstract lang="original">In this paper, we designed a mobile basketball game based on the android platform, and implemented the contents using the unity game engine. A proposed basketball game contents consisted of three types: confrontation, arcade, and last ball, and physical forces such as parabolic and free fall motion were applied to enhance the realistic implementation and a realism of the basketball trajectory. In particular, the physical forces implemented for realism were the distance between the shooting point and the goal-in point on the plane, the time of free fall, and velocity in the horizontal and vertical directions. As a result of implementation, it was confirmed that the principle of the designed physical force is operated according to the design standard, and the basketball trajectory was naturally displayed.</abstract>
